{% schema %}
{
  "name": "Guide Intro (Premium)",
  "tag": "section",
  "class": "section-peptide-intro",
  "settings": [
    {
      "type": "header",
      "content": "Theme Colors"
    },
    { "type": "color", "id": "bg_color", "label": "Section Background", "default": "#fafafb" },
    { "type": "color", "id": "card_bg", "label": "Card Background", "default": "#ffffff" },
    { "type": "color", "id": "accent_color", "label": "Brand Accent (Gold)", "default": "#FBBF24" },
    { "type": "color", "id": "text_color", "label": "Main Text", "default": "#0f172a" }
  ],
  "presets": [{"name": "Guide Intro (Premium)"}]
}
{% endschema %}

<div class="pi-wrapper" id="pi-{{ section.id }}">
  <div class="pi-ambient-glow"></div>
  <div class="pi-container">
    
    <div class="pi-lead-block">
      <div class="pi-lead-accent"></div>
      <p class="pi-lead-text">It can be an intimidating process to reconstitute a peptide for the first time, especially if science never tickled your fancy. Not to mention navigating through different syringe sizes (and truama triggers). However, when it comes down to it, the process of reconstituting a peptide is actually not as complicated as it may seem. Let’s break it down so by the time you finish reading this guide to reconstituting peptides, you know how to do it quickly, and safely.</p>
    </div>
    
    <h2 class="pi-heading">What is Peptide Reconstitution?</h2>
    
    <p class="pi-text">Peptide reconstitution is the process of restoring freeze-dried peptides to their original form by dissolving them with bacteriostatic water to make them active again. In general, reconstituting is the process of restoring something to its original state through dissolving it with water.</p>
    
    <p class="pi-text">Peptides are typically preserved by freeze-drying; which is a process of rapid freezing & vacuuming into ‘lyophilized powder,’ which is what you often see in a vial. Reconstitution is the process of restoring those peptides from the frozen, lyophilized powder and back into their original form, by dissolving them with, ideally, bacteriostatic water.</p>
    
    <p class="pi-text">Bacteriostatic water here prevents any multiplying of bacteria, without destroying the compound itself.</p>
    
    <div class="pi-formula-widget">
      <div class="pi-formula-header">
        <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/><path d="M12 16v-4"/><path d="M12 8h.01"/></svg>
        Scientific Principle
      </div>
      <div class="pi-formula-body">
        <div class="pi-formula-part">
          <span>Lyophilized Powder</span>
        </div>
        <div class="pi-formula-math">+</div>
        <div class="pi-formula-part">
          <span>Bacteriostatic Water</span>
        </div>
        <div class="pi-formula-math">=</div>
        <div class="pi-formula-part pi-part-active">
          <span>Active Peptide</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="pi-formula-footer">
        Peptide reconstitution = mixing peptide + bacteriostatic water
      </div>
    </div>
    
    <p class="pi-text">Thankfully, there is a Peptide Dosage Calculator that resolves the hardest part of this peptide mixing process (the calculating of volume based on desired concentration).</p>
    
    <div class="pi-divider"></div>
    
    <h2 class="pi-heading">Preparation & Safety</h2>
    
    <p class="pi-text">Now we know what is and how to reconstitute a peptide. We also have a tool that gives us the exact quantity of bacteriostatic water to mix. Before we start any of these steps, its crucial to make sure the environment is a very clean, disinfected, and sterilise to prevent infection, and keep the peptide effective.</p>
    
    <p class="pi-text">It’s equally important to work in a quiet, well-lit space, without rushing yourself into completion. Rushing yourself only leads to mistakes (and mistakes here almost always means completely wasting your product and money). Slow and steady always wins the race.</p>
    
    <div class="pi-disclaimer">
      <div class="pi-disclaimer-icon">
        <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M10.29 3.86L1.82 18a2 2 0 0 0 1.71 3h16.94a2 2 0 0 0 1.71-3L13.71 3.86a2 2 0 0 0-3.42 0z"/><line x1="12" y1="9" x2="12" y2="13"/><line x1="12" y1="17" x2="12.01" y2="17"/></svg>
      </div>
      <div class="pi-disclaimer-text">
        <strong>Medical Note:</strong> It's important to consult a professional medical expert if you have a certain condition and are unaware whether it does or doesn't interact with a given peptide.
      </div>
    </div>
    
    <div class="pi-protocol-card" id="pc-guide-section">
      <div class="pi-protocol-glow"></div>
      <div class="pi-step-label">
         <div class="pi-step-badge">
           <span class="pi-pulse-dot"></span>
           Protocol 00
         </div>
         <span class="pi-step-text">Maintain a sterile environment</span>
      </div>
      <p class="pi-explainer">To minimize the risk of contamination and infections, always maintain a sterile environment as step 0. Think of this as a quick but advanced hand-washing:</p>
      
      <ul class="pi-checklist">
        <li>
          <div class="pi-check-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"></polyline></svg></div>
          Wash your hands with soap and warm water.
        </li>
        <li>
          <div class="pi-check-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"></polyline></svg></div>
          Clean the work surface (using alcohol wipes).
        </li>
        <li>
          <div class="pi-check-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"></polyline></svg></div>
          Wipe vials' rubber stoppers (with alcohol pads) and allow the alcohol to dry.
        </li>
        <li>
          <div class="pi-check-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"></polyline></svg></div>
          Don’t touch the bare needle or the vial stoppers after cleaning them.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>

  </div>
</div>

<style>
  #pi-{{ section.id }} {
    --pi-bg: {{ section.settings.bg_color }};
    --pi-card: {{ section.settings.card_bg }};
    --pi-accent: {{ section.settings.accent_color }};
    --pi-text: {{ section.settings.text_color }};
    --pi-muted: var(--color-text-secondary);
    --pi-border: rgba(15, 23, 42, 0.08);
    --pi-font: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "SF Pro Display", "Segoe UI", Roboto, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;
    --pi-radius: var(--nx-radius-lg);
    --pi-shadow-sm: 0 2px 4px -1px rgba(0,0,0,0.03);
    --pi-shadow-md: 0 10px 25px -5px rgba(0,0,0,0.05), 0 8px 10px -6px rgba(0,0,0,0.02);
  }

  .pi-wrapper {
    background-color: var(--pi-bg);
    color: var(--pi-text);
    padding: 60px var(--page-gutter) 40px;
    font-family: var(--pi-font);
    line-height: 1.6;
    position: relative;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .pi-ambient-glow {
    position: absolute;
    top: -10%;
    right: -10%;
    width: 500px;
    height: 500px;
    background: radial-gradient(circle, rgba(251,191,36,0.05) 0%, transparent 60%);
    pointer-events: none;
    z-index: 0;
  }

  .pi-container {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    position: relative;
    z-index: 1;
  }

  .pi-heading {
    font-size: 32px;
    font-weight: 800;
    color: var(--pi-text);
    margin: 50px 0 24px;
    letter-spacing: -0.8px;
  }

  /* Upgraded Lead Text */
  .pi-lead-block {
    position: relative;
    padding: 24px 32px;
    background: var(--color-surface-primary);
    border: 1px solid var(--pi-border);
    border-radius: var(--nx-radius);
    box-shadow: var(--pi-shadow-sm);
    margin-bottom: 40px;
  }
  .pi-lead-accent {
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    top: 24px;
    bottom: 24px;
    width: 4px;
    background: var(--pi-accent);
    border-radius: 0 4px 4px 0;
  }
  .pi-lead-text {
    font-size: 17px;
    color: var(--pi-muted);
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .pi-text {
    font-size: 17px;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    margin-bottom: 20px;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  /* Ultra-Premium Formula Widget */
  .pi-formula-widget {
    background: var(--color-surface-primary);
    border: 1px solid var(--pi-border);
    border-radius: var(--nx-radius);
    padding: 24px;
    margin: 40px 0;
    box-shadow: var(--pi-shadow-md);
    position: relative;
    overflow: hidden;
  }
  .pi-formula-header {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 6px;
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: 800;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 1px;
    color: var(--color-warning-text);
    background: var(--color-warning-bg);
    padding: 6px 12px;
    border-radius: var(--nx-radius-pill);
    margin-bottom: 24px;
    border: 1px solid #fef3c7;
  }
  .pi-formula-body {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 12px;
    margin-bottom: 24px;
  }
  .pi-formula-part {
    background: var(--color-surface-secondary);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border-default);
    padding: 12px 20px;
    border-radius: var(--nx-radius-sm);
    font-size: 15px;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
  }
  .pi-part-active {
    background: var(--color-warning-bg);
    border-color: var(--pi-accent);
    color: var(--color-warning-text);
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-gold-sm);
  }
  .pi-formula-math {
    font-size: 20px;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-text-tertiary);
  }
  .pi-formula-footer {
    border-top: 1px dashed var(--color-border-default);
    padding-top: 16px;
    font-size: 13px;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    font-family: monospace;
  }

  /* Elegant Divider */
  .pi-divider {
    height: 1px;
    background: linear-gradient(90deg, transparent, var(--pi-border) 20%, var(--pi-border) 80%, transparent);
    margin: 60px 0;
  }

  /* Premium Disclaimer Callout */
  .pi-disclaimer {
    display: flex;
    gap: 16px;
    background: linear-gradient(145deg, var(--color-warning-bg), #fef3c7);
    border: 1px solid #fde68a;
    padding: 20px 24px;
    border-radius: var(--nx-radius-md);
    margin: 32px 0;
    box-shadow: inset 0 1px 0 rgba(255,255,255,0.8);
  }
  .pi-disclaimer-icon {
    color: var(--color-warning-text);
    flex-shrink: 0;
    margin-top: 2px;
  }
  .pi-disclaimer-text {
    font-size: 15px;
    color: var(--color-warning-text);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }
  .pi-disclaimer-text strong {
    color: var(--color-accent-dark);
  }

  /* Dashboard Protocol Card */
  .pi-protocol-card {
    background: var(--pi-card);
    border: 1px solid var(--pi-border);
    border-radius: var(--pi-radius);
    padding: 40px;
    margin-top: 40px;
    box-shadow: var(--pi-shadow-md);
    position: relative;
    overflow: hidden;
  }
  .pi-protocol-glow {
    position: absolute;
    top: 0; left: 0; right: 0;
    height: 4px;
    background: linear-gradient(90deg, var(--pi-accent), transparent);
  }
  .pi-step-label {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 16px;
    margin-bottom: 20px;
  }
  .pi-step-badge {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 8px;
    background: var(--color-text-primary);
    color: var(--color-text-inverse);
    padding: 6px 14px;
    border-radius: var(--nx-radius-pill);
    font-size: 12px;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.5px;
  }
  .pi-pulse-dot {
    width: 6px; height: 6px;
    background-color: var(--pi-accent);
    border-radius: 50%;
    box-shadow: 0 0 8px var(--pi-accent);
    animation: pulseStep 2s infinite;
  }
  @keyframes pulseStep {
    0% { transform: scale(1); opacity: 1; }
    50% { transform: scale(1.5); opacity: 0.5; }
    100% { transform: scale(1); opacity: 1; }
  }
  .pi-step-text {
    font-weight: 800;
    font-size: 24px;
    color: var(--pi-text);
    margin: 0;
    letter-spacing: -0.5px;
  }
  .pi-explainer {
    margin: 0 0 24px 0;
    font-size: 16px;
    color: var(--pi-muted);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }
  
  /* Precision Checklist */
  .pi-checklist {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 16px;
  }
  .pi-checklist li {
    display: flex;
    align-items: flex-start;
    gap: 16px;
    font-size: 16px;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    background: var(--color-surface-secondary);
    padding: 16px 20px;
    border-radius: var(--nx-radius-md);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border-default);
    transition: var(--transition-fast);
  }
  .pi-checklist li:hover {
    background: var(--color-surface-primary);
    border-color: var(--color-border-default);
    box-shadow: var(--pi-shadow-sm);
  }
  .pi-check-icon {
    background: var(--color-success-bg);
    color: var(--color-success);
    width: 24px; height: 24px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    flex-shrink: 0;
    margin-top: 2px;
  }
  .pi-check-icon svg { width: 14px; height: 14px; }

  @media(max-width: 600px) {
    .pi-lead-block { padding: 20px; }
    .pi-protocol-card { padding: 24px; }
    .pi-formula-body { flex-direction: column; align-items: flex-start; }
    .pi-formula-math { transform: rotate(90deg); margin: -4px 0 0 16px; }
    .pi-heading { font-size: 28px; }
    .pi-step-label { flex-direction: column; align-items: flex-start; gap: 12px; }
  }
</style>